The Forms Designer does not currently support editing the columns of a JTable.
To define table rows and columns, you have to create a TableModel.
In your code you would get the table from the form and call setModel with your specialized TableModel

For example: 
    JTable table = m_form.getTable( "mytable");
    table.setModel( new MyTableModel() );

See the JTable tutorial:
http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/uiswing/components/table.html
